Cook pasta in a large pot of boiling salted water until al dente. Drain. In a large skillet, cook ground beef, onion, and mushrooms. Drain grease. Mix in garlic salt, ground black pepper, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, and tomato sauce. Simmer for 30 minutes. In a greased 2 quart casserole dish, layer half of the cooked egg noodles, then half of the sauce mixture, followed by half of the grated cheese. Repeat. Bake in a preheated 375 degree (190 degree C) oven for 20 to 30 minutes.